Air France  and  Deutsche Lufthansa AG 
are interested in buying a stake in Polskie Linie Lotnicze LOT
SA from the Polish government, Dziennik Gazeta Prawna reported,
citing an unnamed person in the Treasury Ministry.  Turkish Airlines  is so far the only identified company the
Polish government is talking to about selling the LOT stake, the
newspaper said, citing Treasury Ministry spokeswoman Magdalena Kobos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
